ant to the defense's limited-scope argument.\\n\\n[plaintiff] PX-R4 Ukrainska Pravda Ukraine-side confirmation\\nSource: Ukrainska Pravda. Title in page metadata: Ukrainian ombudsman says 1,000-for-1,000 prisoner exchange stalled because of Russia's stance. Author: Tetyana Oliynyk. Published: 2026-05-12T23:43:00+03:00. URL: https://www.pravda.com.ua/eng/news/2026/05/12/8034416/\\n\\nExtracted facts from metadata and JSON-LD articleBody:\\n- Dmytro Lubinets, Ukraine's Parliamentary Commissioner for Human Rights, said Ukraine had submitted lists for the planned prisoner exchange and that Russia was delaying the process.\\n- The article quotes Lubinets as saying that even when an agreement is reached with Russia, Ukraine can never be 100% sure Russia will honor it, but work and negotiations continued every day.\\n- Background section reports that on 8 May, U.S. President Donald Trump announced a three-day ceasefire in the war between Ukraine and Russia.\\n- Background section reports that President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said a 1,000-for-1,000 prisoner swap would take place on 9 May and confirmed the U.S. president's announcement regarding a ceasefire with Russia on 9-11 May.\\n- Background section reports that Ukraine officially granted Russia permission to hold its Victory Day parade as part of the ceasefire arrangements.\\n- Background section reports that Russia also agreed to support Trump's ceasefire initiative for 9-11 May and the prisoner exchange.\\n\\nSource-chain notes: This is Ukrainian media reporting, not the direct presidential decree or direct Zelenskyy social post. It is useful as Ukraine-side corroboration and for adverse context: post-period implementation of the prisoner swap was disputed, and Ukraine expressed skepticism about Russian performance.\\n\\n[defendant] DX-S1 Direct Ukrainian decree narrow scope\\nSource: Official website of the President of Ukraine. URL: https://www.president.gov.ua/documents/3742026-59389\\n\\nTitle shown on page: Decree 