does not by itself prove no political agreement existed, but it undercuts the proposition's requirement of a general halt in military engagement by showing continued theater activity during the alleged pause.\\n\\n[plaintiff] PX-R3 Al Jazeera/Reuters all-kinetic-activity confirmation\\nSource: Al Jazeera, Reuters. Title: Trump announces three-day ceasefire in Russia-Ukraine war. Published: 2026-05-08; modified 2026-05-09. URL: https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/5/8/trump-announces-three-day-ceasefire-in-russia-ukraine-war\\n\\nExtracted facts from page text and metadata:\\n- Description: truce would include swap of 1,000 prisoners of war from each country.\\n- The article reports that U.S. President Donald Trump said there would be a three-day ceasefire in the war between Russia and Ukraine, lasting Saturday to Monday.\\n- It reports Trump's post announcing a three-day ceasefire for May 9, 10, and 11 in the war between Russia and Ukraine.\\n- It reports that soon after, Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy confirmed on X that a three-day truce had been arranged as part of U.S. efforts to negotiate an end to the war.\\n- It reports Russian presidential aide Yuri Ushakov said an agreement was reached through telephone contacts with the U.S. administration and that U.S. representatives were in contact with Kyiv.\\n- It reports Trump said the ceasefire would include a suspension of all kinetic activity and a prisoner swap of 1,000 prisoners from each country, and that Zelenskyy also confirmed the prisoner swap would take place.\\n- It reports Ushakov stressed the ceasefire was for three days, not longer.\\n\\nSource-chain notes: This is secondary reporting with Reuters attribution on the page. It is not itself an official government record, but it identifies official statements by Trump, Zelenskyy, and Russian aide Ushakov and corroborates the case packet's official-source and secondary-reporting summaries. The article also confirms the temporary nature of the pause, which is relevant to the defense's limited-scope argument.\\n\\n[plaintiff] PX-R4 Ukrainska Pravda Ukraine-side confirmation\\nSource: Ukrainska Pravda. Title in page metadata: Ukrainian ombudsman says 1,000-for-1,000 prisoner exchange stalled because of Russia's stance. Author: Tetyana Oliynyk. Published: 2026-05-12T23:43:00+03:00. URL: https://www.pravda.com.ua/eng/news/2026/05/12/8034416/\\n\\nExtracted facts from metadata and JSON-LD articleBody:\\n- Dmytro Lubinets, Ukraine's Parliamentary Commissioner for Human Rights, said Ukraine had submitted lists for the planned prisoner exchange and that Russia was delaying the process.\\n- The article quotes Lubinets as saying that even when an agreement is reached with Russia, Ukraine can never be 100% sure Russia will honor it, but work and negotiations continued every day.\\n- Background section reports that on 8 May, U.S. President Donald Trump announced a three-day ceasefire in the war between Ukraine and Russia.\\n- Background section reports that President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said a 1,000-for-1,000 prisoner swap would take place on 9 May and confirmed the U.S. president's announcement regarding a ceasefire with Russia on 9-11 May.\\n- Background section reports that Ukraine officially granted Russia permission to hold its Victory Day parade as part of the ceasefire arrangements.\\n- Background section reports that Russia also agreed to support Trump's ceasefire initiative for 9-11 May and the prisoner exchange.\\n\\nSource-chain notes: This is Ukrainian media reporting, not the direct presidential decree or direct Zelenskyy social post. It is useful as Ukraine-side corroboration and for adverse context: post-period implementation of the prisoner swap was disputed, and Ukraine expressed skepticism about Russian performance.\\n\\n[defendant] DX-S1 Direct Ukrainian decree narrow scope\\nSource: Official website of the President of Ukraine. URL: https://www.president.gov.ua/documents/3742026-59389\\n\\nTitle shown 