{"aar_log_filter":{"content_index":0,"dropped_prefix_bytes":2468,"field":"text","message":"earlier repeated message_update events dropped","replaced_fields":2,"response_id":"gen-1782791486-vO6YfKVhfpBiYv2gMHoS","tail_bytes":2},"assistantMessageEvent":{"contentIndex":0,"delta":".\"","partial":{"api":"openai-completions","content":[{"text":".\"","type":"text"}],"model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1782791486-vO6YfKVhfpBiYv2gMHoS","role":"assistant","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782791485604,"usage":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"input":0,"output":0,"total":0},"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0}},"type":"text_delta"},"message":{"api":"openai-completions","content":[{"text":".\"","type":"text"}],"model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1782791486-vO6YfKVhfpBiYv2gMHoS","role":"assistant","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782791485604,"usage":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"input":0,"output":0,"total":0},"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0}},"type":"message_update"}
{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_start","contentIndex":1,"partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my examination of the admitted evidence, I now have a comprehensive understanding of the record. Let me analyze the key points:\n\n**Key Evidence Summary:**\n\n1. **Market Rule Requirements**: The proposition requires a \"publicly announced and mutually agreed halt in military engagement that constituted a general pause in the conflict\" and excludes \"humanitarian pauses\" and \"limited agreements.\"\n\n2. **Russian Official Acceptance**: The official Russian source shows Yury Ushakov stating Russia accepted the U.S.-proposed ceasefire \"for the purpose of conducting a prisoner exchange\" during May 9-11.\n\n3. **Ukrainian Official Source**: The direct Ukrainian presidential decree is narrowly limited to permitting the Moscow parade and excluding Red Square from targeting plans during the parade - not a theater-wide ceasefire.\n\n4. **Media Reporting**: Multiple credible sources (Al Jazeera/Reuters, Defense News, Ukrainska Pravda) report Trump's announcement of a three-day ceasefire with \"suspension of all kinetic activity\" and Zelenskyy's confirmation.\n\n5. **Battlefield Evidence**: ISW assessments show continued limited offensive operations across the theater on both May 9 and May 10, with mutual violation accusations and activity that \"decreased but did not cease.\"\n\n**Analysis:**\n\nThe critical issue is whether the arrangement constituted a \"general pause in the conflict\" as required by the market rule. While there was clearly public discussion and political announcements about a ceasefire, the evidence shows:\n\n1. The only direct Ukrainian official instrument (the presidential decree) is geographically and temporally narrow, focused only on Red Square/parade security.\n\n2. The Russian official framing emphasizes the prisoner-exchange purpose.\n\n3. Battlefield monitoring demonstrates continued military engagement across the theater during the alleged ceasefire period.\n\n4. The arrangement appears to be more consistent with a limited humanitarian/prisoner-exchange pause tied to Victory Day ceremonies rather than a general halt in military engagement.\n\nOn a preponderance standard, the evidence weighs more heavily toward the arrangement being a limited, purpose-specific pause rather than the qualifying \"general pause in the conflict\" required by the proposition. The battlefield evidence showing continued operations is particularly probative of whether a general halt actually occurred.\n\nBased on this analysis, I will vote \"not_demonstrated.\""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cb0a","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The record shows a temporary, prisoner-exchange-focused arrangement with continued theater-wide military operations. The Ukrainian decree is narrowly limited to Red Square targeting, and battlefield evidence demonstrates ongoing engagement, falling short of the required general pause in military engagement.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"not_demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The record shows a temporary, prisoner-exchange-focused arrangement with continued theater-wide military operations. The Ukrainian decree is narrowly limited to Red Square targeting, and battlefield evidence demonstrates ongoing engagement, falling short of the required general pause in military engagement.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782791485604,"responseId":"gen-1782791486-vO6YfKVhfpBiYv2gMHoS"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my examination of the admitted evidence, I now have a comprehensive understanding of the record. Let me analyze the key points:\n\n**Key Evidence Summary:**\n\n1. **Market Rule Requirements**: The proposition requires a \"publicly announced and mutually agreed halt in military engagement that constituted a general pause in the conflict\" and excludes \"humanitarian pauses\" and \"limited agreements.\"\n\n2. **Russian Official Acceptance**: The official Russian source shows Yury Ushakov stating Russia accepted the U.S.-proposed ceasefire \"for the purpose of conducting a prisoner exchange\" during May 9-11.\n\n3. **Ukrainian Official Source**: The direct Ukrainian presidential decree is narrowly limited to permitting the Moscow parade and excluding Red Square from targeting plans during the parade - not a theater-wide ceasefire.\n\n4. **Media Reporting**: Multiple credible sources (Al Jazeera/Reuters, Defense News, Ukrainska Pravda) report Trump's announcement of a three-day ceasefire with \"suspension of all kinetic activity\" and Zelenskyy's confirmation.\n\n5. **Battlefield Evidence**: ISW assessments show continued limited offensive operations across the theater on both May 9 and May 10, with mutual violation accusations and activity that \"decreased but did not cease.\"\n\n**Analysis:**\n\nThe critical issue is whether the arrangement constituted a \"general pause in the conflict\" as required by the market rule. While there was clearly public discussion and political announcements about a ceasefire, the evidence shows:\n\n1. The only direct Ukrainian official instrument (the presidential decree) is geographically and temporally narrow, focused only on Red Square/parade security.\n\n2. The Russian official framing emphasizes the prisoner-exchange purpose.\n\n3. Battlefield monitoring demonstrates continued military engagement across the theater during the alleged ceasefire period.\n\n4. The arrangement appears to be more consistent with a limited humanitarian/prisoner-exchange pause tied to Victory Day ceremonies rather than a general halt in military engagement.\n\nOn a preponderance standard, the evidence weighs more heavily toward the arrangement being a limited, purpose-specific pause rather than the qualifying \"general pause in the conflict\" required by the proposition. The battlefield evidence showing continued operations is particularly probative of whether a general halt actually occurred.\n\nBased on this analysis, I will vote \"not_demonstrated.\""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cb0a","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The record shows a temporary, prisoner-exchange-focused arrangement with continued theater-wide military operations. The Ukrainian decree is narrowly limited to Red Square targeting, and battlefield evidence demonstrates ongoing engagement, falling short of the required general pause in military engagement.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"not_demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The record shows a temporary, prisoner-exchange-focused arrangement with continued theater-wide military operations. The Ukrainian decree is narrowly limited to Red Square targeting, and battlefield evidence demonstrates ongoing engagement, falling short of the required general pause in military engagement.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782791485604,"responseId":"gen-1782791486-vO6YfKVhfpBiYv2gMHoS"}}
{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_delta","contentIndex":1,"delta":"","partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my examination of the admitted evidence, I now have a comprehensive understanding of the record. Let me analyze the key points:\n\n**Key Evidence Summary:**\n\n1. **Market Rule Requirements**: The proposition requires a \"publicly announced and mutually agreed halt in military engagement that constituted a general pause in the conflict\" and excludes \"humanitarian pauses\" and \"limited agreements.\"\n\n2. **Russian Official Acceptance**: The official Russian source shows Yury Ushakov stating Russia accepted the U.S.-proposed ceasefire \"for the purpose of conducting a prisoner exchange\" during May 9-11.\n\n3. **Ukrainian Official Source**: The direct Ukrainian presidential decree is narrowly limited to permitting the Moscow parade and excluding Red Square from targeting plans during the parade - not a theater-wide ceasefire.\n\n4. **Media Reporting**: Multiple credible sources (Al Jazeera/Reuters, Defense News, Ukrainska Pravda) report Trump's announcement of a three-day ceasefire with \"suspension of all kinetic activity\" and Zelenskyy's confirmation.\n\n5. **Battlefield Evidence**: ISW assessments show continued limited offensive operations across the theater on both May 9 and May 10, with mutual violation accusations and activity that \"decreased but did not cease.\"\n\n**Analysis:**\n\nThe critical issue is whether the arrangement constituted a \"general pause in the conflict\" as required by the market rule. While there was clearly public discussion and political announcements about a ceasefire, the evidence shows:\n\n1. The only direct Ukrainian official instrument (the presidential decree) is geographically and temporally narrow, focused only on Red Square/parade security.\n\n2. The Russian official framing emphasizes the prisoner-exchange purpose.\n\n3. Battlefield monitoring demonstrates continued military engagement across the theater during the alleged ceasefire period.\n\n4. The arrangement appears to be more consistent with a limited humanitarian/prisoner-exchange pause tied to Victory Day ceremonies rather than a general halt in military engagement.\n\nOn a preponderance standard, the evidence weighs more heavily toward the arrangement being a limited, purpose-specific pause rather than the qualifying \"general pause in the conflict\" required by the proposition. The battlefield evidence showing continued operations is particularly probative of whether a general halt actually occurred.\n\nBased on this analysis, I will vote \"not_demonstrated.\""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cb0a","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The record shows a temporary, prisoner-exchange-focused arrangement with continued theater-wide military operations. The Ukrainian decree is narrowly limited to Red Square targeting, and battlefield evidence demonstrates ongoing engagement, falling short of the required general pause in military engagement.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"not_demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The record shows a temporary, prisoner-exchange-focused arrangement with continued theater-wide military operations. The Ukrainian decree is narrowly limited to Red Square targeting, and battlefield evidence demonstrates ongoing engagement, falling short of the required general pause in military engagement.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782791485604,"responseId":"gen-1782791486-vO6YfKVhfpBiYv2gMHoS"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"